        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-01 10:46:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAny idea why this fix works? \nI think this worked fine before?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "bf242fa8d16ae57eb8aa44e2bbd69bd132f1d224",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5072,
          "name": "Patrik Buhr",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "patrik.buhr@est.tech",
          "username": "PatrikBuhr"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-01 11:05:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Any idea why this fix works? \n> I think this worked fine before?\n\nThe test has not been included in the automatic tests, so it has probably been run by me locally. \nIt is a new test for the new V2 of the NBI. \nThe problem was that the synchronization could be non-yet-finnshed when the test was running. So it was interfering with the result (the number of policy types for a ric was not the expected). \nNow the test waits until the RIC state is  \"synchronized\".",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d5e2c5bb068de765c4b9f2d65f3f9848f79368c3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5072,
          "name": "Patrik Buhr",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "patrik.buhr@est.tech",
          "username": "PatrikBuhr"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-01 11:12:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Any idea why this fix works? \n> I think this worked fine before?\n\nMaybe I misunderstood you question. The test classes named ApplicationTestV1 and ApplicationTestV2 were \nnot run by mvn test. But removing 'V1' resp. 'V2' from the class names solved that. I do not have a clue why that was the case; some kind of crazyness in the jupiter test engine I guess.  \n\n\nThe instability is fixed by this commit: \nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ccsdk/oran/+/111931",
        "patchset_number": 2
      }
    ]
  }
